SIMPLE: dictation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dictation
<hw>Dic*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dictatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of dictating; the
act or practice of prescribing; also that which is dictated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It affords security against the <qex>dictation</qex> of laws.</q>
<rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The speaking to, or the giving orders to, in an
overbearing manner; authoritative utterance; <as>as, his habit, even
with friends, was that of <ex>dictation</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dictator</ent>⟦br⟧
